If you don't have a #toaster{}, preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the burger buns.

Drain the @Halloumi{225%grams}, then slice into 1cm batons. Place into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet} and @Plain Flour{1%tbsp} with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Season with @ground black pepper{pinch}.

Lay your chicken breast in the bowl, then toss to coat evenly. Repeat for the other breast(s). IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the chicken has 1 min left, drizzle over the @Honey{2%tbsp} and turn to coat.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board, cover with #foil{} and rest until ready to serve.

While the chicken fries, zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Drain the @Sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

In a medium bowl, combine the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams}, sweetcorn, half the lime juice, a pinch of lime zest and half the @Mayonnaise{96%grams}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}.

Taste and season with more lime juice and zest if needed.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet} and toss to coat.

Wipe out the (now empty) #chicken frying pan{} and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{for frying}.

Once hot, fry the halloumi until golden, turning frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When everything's nearly ready, if you're using the toaster, halve the @Burger Buns{2} and toast in your toaster until golden.

If you're using the oven, pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reserve a handful of @Baby Leaf Mix{20%grams} for the burgers, then add the remaining leaves to the slaw and toss to combine.

> Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Spread the remaining mayo over the bun bases and the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%grams} over the bun lids.

Share the reserved leaves between the bun bases, then top with the peri peri chicken and sandwich shut with the lids.

Serve with the halloumi fries and corn slaw alongside.

Enjoy!